abstract: Joe Biden is "healthy, vigorous" and "fit to successfully execute the duties of the Presidency," according to a doctor's report released Tuesday by the 77-year-old former vice president.
snippet: Joe Biden is "healthy, vigorous" and "fit to successfully execute the duties of the Presidency," according to a doctor's report released Tuesday by the 77-year-old former vice president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joe Biden is "healthy, vigorous" and "fit to successfully execute the duties of the Presidency," according to a doctor's report released Tuesday by the 77-year-old former vice president.

abstract: Former Vice President Joe Biden is healthy enough to undertake the duties of the U.S. presidency, his doctor said on Tuesday in a health report released by the Democrat's campaign.
snippet: Former Vice President Joe Biden is healthy enough to undertake the duties of the U.S. presidency, his doctor said on Tuesday in a health report released by the Democrat's campaign.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former Vice President Joe Biden is healthy enough to undertake the duties of the U.S. presidency, his doctor said on Tuesday in a health report released by the Democrat's campaign.
headline_main: Biden, 77, Is Healthy and Fit to Serve as President, His Doctor Says
headline_print_headline: Biden, 77, Is Healthy and Fit to Serve as President, His Doctor Says

abstract: During a seven-event swing in southeastern Iowa over the past several days, Democratic U.S. presidential contender Elizabeth Warren took more than 60 questions from voters on everything from sustainable farming to Medicare for All.
snippet: During a seven-event swing in southeastern Iowa over the past several days, Democratic U.S. presidential contender Elizabeth Warren took more than 60 questions from voters on everything from sustainable farming to Medicare for All.
lead_paragraph: KEOKUK, Iowa — During a seven-event swing in southeastern Iowa over the past several days, Democratic U.S. presidential contender Elizabeth Warren took more than 60 questions from voters on everything from sustainable farming to Medicare for All.
headline_main: On the 2020 Campaign Trail, Little Talk of Impeachment Ahead of Historic Vote
headline_print_headline: On the 2020 Campaign Trail, Little Talk of Impeachment Ahead of Historic Vote

abstract: A business associate of Rudy Giuliani received a $1 million payment in September from an indicted Ukrainian oligarch who is a fugitive from justice in the U.S., federal prosecutors revealed Tuesday.
snippet: A business associate of Rudy Giuliani received a $1 million payment in September from an indicted Ukrainian oligarch who is a fugitive from justice in the U.S., federal prosecutors revealed Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A business associate of Rudy Giuliani received a $1 million payment in September from an indicted Ukrainian oligarch who is a fugitive from justice in the U.S., federal prosecutors revealed Tuesday.
headline_main: Giuliani Associate Got $1 Million From Indicted Ukrainian

abstract: The CBS game “Survivor” ends its 39th edition this week reeling from controversy over its first-ever forced removal of a contestant, a Hollywood agent sent packing after young women complained about inappropriate touching.

abstract: President Trump sent a letter on Tuesday to Speaker Nancy Pelosi expressing his “most powerful protest” against the impeachment process. The House is expected to vote on two articles of impeachment against Mr. Trump on Wednesday.

abstract: The top U.S. diplomat in Ukraine will be leaving his post at the beginning of next year after a term convulsed by the impeachment inquiry into President Donald Trump, two officials said Tuesday.
snippet: The top U.S. diplomat in Ukraine will be leaving his post at the beginning of next year after a term convulsed by the impeachment inquiry into President Donald Trump, two officials said Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The top U.S. diplomat in Ukraine will be leaving his post at the beginning of next year after a term convulsed by the impeachment inquiry into President Donald Trump, two officials said Tuesday.
headline_main: US Envoy in Ukraine Set to Leave After Impeachment Testimony

headline_main: Before a Historic Impeachment: ‘Right vs. Wrong’

abstract: The 1992 feminist sensation “Women Who Run With the Wolves” has returned, as a new generation of artists embrace women’s bodies in all their hormonal, bloody glory.
snippet: The 1992 feminist sensation “Women Who Run With the Wolves” has returned, as a new generation of artists embrace women’s bodies in all their hormonal, bloody glory.
lead_paragraph: I first spied the book last spring, in the lap of a vaguely witchy young woman pinched between two men on the subway. Soon the book disappeared into a woven bag, her shoulder brushed against mine, and it was as if she had initiated me into a secret club. After that, I saw the book everywhere: in the hands of a tattooed solo diner while she ate a game bird in a Texas restaurant; nestled with the new releases on female rage in a Brooklyn bookstore; on Lana Del Rey’s Instagram.
